tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Laboratory results show good glycemic control and normal renal function markers, except for mildly decreased creatinine, which is not clinically significant. Lipid profile reveals elevated total and LDL cholesterol, indicating increased cardiovascular risk. Electrolytes, calcium, and urine microalbumin/creatinine ratio are within normal limits. Recommend addressing hypercholesterolemia and monitoring cardiovascular risk factors.
